## {{ rule.title }}

[26 U.S.C. § 1256](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1256&num=0&edition=prelim) contracts — regulated futures, foreign-currency contracts, broad-based index options, dealer equity options, and dealer securities futures — get special treatment. They are marked to market at year end (so unrealized gain/loss is recognized) and the resulting net is split 40 % short-term / 60 % long-term regardless of the actual holding period. [Form 6781](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-6781) is the worksheet; the split numbers carry to [Schedule D](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-schedule-d-form-1040).

{% set split = rule.outputs[0].value | from_json -%}
For 2025 the [§ 1256](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1256&num=0&edition=prelim) net mark-to-market total is **{{ split.total_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**. Applying the statutory split:

- Short-term portion (40 % per § 1256(a)(3)(A)): **{{ split.short_term_usd | money(currency="USD") }}** — combines with Box A/B/H short-term gains and losses at US25-05.
- Long-term portion (60 % per § 1256(a)(3)(B)): **{{ split.long_term_usd | money(currency="USD") }}** — combines with Box D/K long-term gains, losses, and 1099-DIV box 2a distributions.

The [§ 1256](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1256&num=0&edition=prelim) split character does not depend on how long you actually held the contract; it is fixed by statute.

